10. Good luck
    Send / Receive Mails
    ====================

    At this stage, your setup is ready to send mails to the outside world. To receive
    mails, you need to create your actual domain (instead of example.com) using vadddomain
    and setup a mail exchanger record for your domain (MX record).
    To send mails, you can either use SMTP or use a sendmail replacement -
    @indimaildir@/bin/sendmail.sh

    You may also want to link sendmail to @indimaildir@/bin/sendmail.sh

    % sudo rm /usr/sbin/sendmail
    % ln -s @indimaildir@/bin/sendmail.sh /usr/sbin/sendmail

    If you link sendmail to @indimaildir@/bin/sendmail.sh, then
    you can do the following to send a test mail.

    % ( echo 'First M. Last'; uname -a) | mail -s "IndiMail Installation" mbhangui@gmail.com

    Replace First M. Last with your name.

    If you have questions about indimail, join the indimail mailing list; You can also use the
    tracker to track all your requests.

